com.ryanbrooks.expandablerecyclerview.ViewHolder

Class ParentViewHolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v7.widget.RecyclerView.ViewHolder
      • com.ryanbrooks.expandablerecyclerview.ViewHolder.ParentViewHolder

  • public class ParentViewHolder
extends android.support.v7.widget.RecyclerView.ViewHolder
    ParentViewHolder that extends the Base RecyclerView ViewHolder. All expansion animation and click handling is done here.
    Since:
    5/27/2015

    • Method Detail

      • setCustomClickableViewOnly

        public void setCustomClickableViewOnly(int clickableViewId)
        Setter for a custom Clickable view rather than the Parent item. By calling this method, the Parent item is no longer responsible for triggering the expansion. The user should pass in the id of the view that they wish to be the expansion trigger.
        Parameters:
        clickableViewId -

      • setCustomClickableViewAndItem

        public void setCustomClickableViewAndItem(int clickableViewId)
        Setter for a custom Clickable view and the Parent item. By calling this method, the Parent item and the clickable view are responsible for triggering the expansion. This means that either can be clicked and an expansion will occur. The user should pass in an id of the view they wish to set as the clickable expansion button.
        Parameters:
        clickableViewId -

      • setAnimationDuration

        public void setAnimationDuration(long animationDuration)

      • cancelAnimation

        public void cancelAnimation()
        Disables animation of the custom clickable button.

      • setMainItemClickToExpand

        public void setMainItemClickToExpand()
        Sets the Parent only as the trigger to expand the item. Also disables rotation of the custom clickable view.

      • isExpanded

        Returns if the item is currently expanded.

      • setExpanded
